{
  "texts": [
    "An example of a reconstructive approach to self-supervised learning is the denoising autoencoder [17] (Fig. 3a).",
    "In the image colourization task, coloured images are generated from greyscale images, which is made possible by the availability of a dataset of coloured images [18].",
    "Inpainting of redacted patches of images is another example of a reconstructive pretext task [19] (Fig. 3b).",
    "Predictive methodsMany custom pretext tasks have been proposed for computer vision that involve learning a specific transformation applied to images.",
    "A stochastic transformation is applied to each example, and the learner's task is to predict or to undo the transformation."
  ]
}